# Big Klimenetsky Island
|}

The Kondopoga Bay is deeply carved in the land by glacial process. The  upper part of the bay receives about 90% of the waters of the [[Suna River]] via the Nigozersky (Kondopozhsky) Canal.  The bay also receives [[waste water]], most of which comes from the Kondopoga paper mill.<ref>[http://www.kondopoga.ru/2019-kondopozhskaya-guba.html]</ref>
[[File:Кондопожская губа.jpg|250 px|right|thumb|Kondopoga Bay, 2010]]
A city of [[Kondopoga]] is by the northern tip of the bay.

The bay has numerous rock islands, the largest being Suisari.

